										"string" : "This page explains how Python objects can define inspector views directly in Python using the `gtoolkit_bridge` package and the `@gtView` decorator. It summarizes the available remote view builders (`list`, `columnedList`, `textEditor`, `columnedTree`, `forward`, `empty`), shows small examples of each, and points to Remote Phlow as the underlying model. Read this when you want Python-side custom inspectors, not just code execution."
