										},
										"string" : "This page explains what actually comes back from Python: primitive values in some cases, but most often {{gtClass:PBProxyObject}} instances backed by Python-side object identifiers. It contrasts the Remote and Proxy inspector perspectives, shows how to access attributes and call methods on proxies, explains the conversion behavior for primitive/composite values, and introduces mirror subclasses of {{gtClass:PBProxyObject}} for adding GT-side behavior and views to specific Python classes."
